{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_78","type":"agent_message","text":"The old `spring-context` metadata has a clue: it explicitly registers dynamic proxies for annotation types like `@Configuration`, `@Bean`, `@Import`, and `@ImportResource`. Boot’s annotations used by this module are missing equivalent proxy entries, and that would explain why Spring can scan the class files but still fail to synthesize the Boot annotations into active configuration metadata. I’m adding those proxy registrations now."}}
